PAL16L8
32016 (16 BIT INTERFACE) FOR IBM PC
(C) 1986,87 GEORGE SCOLARO
SECOND CONTROL PAL FOR 74LS646 32016-PC PARALLEL LINK   16:42 870103
/ISEL IA1 IA2 /IOR /IOW FULL0 FULL1 /CWAITS SREQ GND
IRESET /SREQC /FIX /ID0 /ISELP /RSTI /CWAIT /INT32 /IOCHRDY VCC

IF (VCC) RSTI	= ISEL * IA1 * /IA2 * IOW   ; SOFTWARE RESET
		+ RSTI * /INT32	* /IRESET   ; LATCH UP IF NOT POWER ON RESET

IF (VCC) INT32	= ISEL * /IA1 * IA2 * IOW	;32032 INTERRUPT FROM IBM PC

IF (CWAITS) CWAIT = CWAITS

IF (ISEL * IA1 * IOR) ID0 = FULL0 * /IA2	;DATA STILL PRESENT
			  + FULL1 * /IA2
			  + SREQ * IA2

IF (VCC) ISELP	= ISEL * /IA1 * /IA2

IF (FIX) IOCHRDY = FIX				;MAKE IBM WAIT

IF (VCC) FIX	= IOR * ISEL * /IA1 * /IA2 * /FULL0 * /FULL1	;WAIT ON READ
		+ IOW * ISEL * /IA1 * /IA2 * FULL0 * FULL1	;WAIT ON WRITE

IF (VCC) SREQC	= ISEL * IA1 * IA2 * IOW	;RESET SREQ FF
		+ RSTI				;SOFTWARE 32000 RESET
		+ IRESET			;OR POWER ON RESET

FUNCTION TABLE
/CWAIT /CWAITS /ISEL IA1 IA2 /IOR /IOW FULL0 FULL1 /SREQC SREQ
/FIX /ID0 IRESET /RSTI /INT32 /IOCHRDY /ISELP
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
XX L HL XL XX XX X X XL X X X	;SOFTWARE RESET
XX L LH XL XX XX X X XX L X X	;SOFTWARE INT32
XX L HL LX HX XX X L XX X X X	;CHECK FOR FULL0 IN SOFTWARE
XX L HL LX XH XX X L XX X X X	;CHECK FOR FULL1 IN SOFTWARE
XX L HH LX XX XH X L XX X X X	;CHECK FOR SREQ IN SOFTWARE
XX L LL LH LL XX L X XX X X X	;GENERATE FIX SIGNAL FOR READ
XX L LL HL HH XX L X XX X X X	;DITTO FOR WRITE
XX L LL LH LL XX L X XX X L X	;APPLY IOCHRDY IF FIX ON READ
XX L LL HL HH XX L X XX X L X	;APPLY IOCHRDY IF FIX ON WRITE
XX L HH XL XX LX X X XX X X X	;GENERATE SREQC BY SOFTWARE
XX L LL XX XX XX X X XX X X L	;CHECK FOR ISELP
XX H XX XX XX XX X X XX X X H 	;SHOULD NOT ISELP
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
This pal generates the clock signals for the 74LS646 devices on the IBM PC
side. This pal also can generate an interrupt request on the 32032 side under
control of the IBM PC.
It also generates IOCHRDY (wait states on the IBM PC) if the 74LS646's are
either empty on a read or full on a write.
